cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM 

This paper focuses on image-based localization, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with robotics (cs.RO) since accurate localization is crucial for robot navigation. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on three challenging datasets, which suggests that it may also fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
